      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Retin A, or retinoic acid, is a medication commonly used to reduce wrinkles and treat severe acne. How many different isomers arising from <i>E,Z</i> double-bond isomerizations are possible?</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down-30\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBZzhTIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--1f48b29928092d369bd8f875fa8e02669a7fa471/OChem_07_EC_031.jpg\" alt=\"The structure of retin A (retinoic acid): one double bond in a ring, and four double bonds in a long substituent chain, each with two different substituents at each carbon.\">",
